data.enText: to give sb information so that they understand sth better

data.chText: 她未向他讲明自己的出身背景。
data.enText: She didn't enlighten him about her background.

data.chText: 那次面谈让人很受启发。
data.enText: It was a very enlightening interview.

simple_means.memory_skill: en 进入…之中；包围 + light 光 + en 进入…之中；包围 → 进入光明 → 启发

tr: make free from confusion or ambiguity
example: Clear up the question of who is at fault
Can you enlighten me--I don't understand this proposal

value.def: To enlighten someone means to give them more knowledge and greater understanding about something.

example.ex: A few dedicated doctors have fought for years to enlighten the profession...
example.tran: 一些有献身精神的医生多年来一直努力指导业内同仁。

example.ex: If you know what is wrong with her, please enlighten me.
example.tran: 如果你知道她出什么问题了，请告诉我。

example.ex: ...an enlightening talk on the work done at the animal park...
example.tran: 介绍动物园工作情况的启发性讲话

example.ex: It can be an enormously enlightening and exciting experience.
example.tran: 它会是一次非常有启发性、令人兴奋的经历。
